The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Wednesday, December 17, 2003 				 Suicide after torture
																								Diamond Harbour, Dec. 16: A 20-year old housewife committed suicide here last night, unable to bear her in-laws torture.																								Tumpa Mondal, who had poured kerosene and set herself afire at her Kalatalahat residence, about 70 km from Calcutta, was rushed to the Diamond Harbour Sadar Hospital. She succumbed to injuries early this morning. 																								Police have recovered a suicide note in which Tumpa accused husband Tapas and her in-laws of goading her to death. She also scribbled accusations against the in-laws on a wall with lip-stick.Tapas and his parents were arrested and later remanded in custody. 																								Married two-and-a-half years ago, Tumpa had a one-and-a-half-year old daughter. Neighbours, who saw smoke billowing from the bedroom window, said they quarrelled often. Tapas, who works in a factory, told the police that when Tumpa set herself ablaze, he was at work and his father was away from home. His mother had taken the child out.
